.TH TOP 2 "2025" "Nightingale" "Nightingale System Calls"
.SH NAME
top \- display process/thread information
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <unistd.h>
.PP
.BI "int top(int " show_threads ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B top()
prints information about running processes and threads to the kernel log.
This is primarily a debugging system call.
.PP
If
.I show_threads
is non-zero, information about individual threads is displayed.
Otherwise, only process-level information is shown.
.PP
The information includes process IDs, thread IDs, states, and other
kernel-internal details.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns 0 on success, or \-1 on error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR procstate (2),
.BR getpid (2)
